31/01/2005
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Severe winter weather has led to emergency situations in several parts of the Balkans during the past few days. In Albania, intense snowfalls have isolated whole villages in the northeast. The army is helping to clear roads and government assistance has been offered to the hardest hit regions. Power has been lost in a number of mountain villages in Bulgaria, Macedonia and Serbia-Montenegro. In Bulgaria and Romania, Black Sea ports were closed to traffic Monday (31 January). (Standart, Danas - 31/01/05; Albanian News, A1 TV, HINA - 29/01/05) 
